    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="529"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/8–1546: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Attlee</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to"
                            >Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="44" xml:id="d529fn44">Copy transmitted to Mr. Acheson by the British
                        Minister in Washington (Balfour) on August 15.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-15">15 August
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Personal and Top Secret. Thank you for your personal message of August 13th [<hi
                        rend="italic">12th</hi>]. I have now received from the Foreign Secretary in
                    Paris a copy of the message sent by the State Department to Mr. Byrnes and Mr.
                    Harriman. We are discussing these proposals and it will probably take a few days
                    before we can give our views on them.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
